.TH "nanddev_markbad" 9 "nanddev_markbad" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nanddev_markbad \- Mark a block as bad
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nanddev_markbad
.BI "(struct nand_device *nand "  ","
.BI "const struct nand_pos *pos "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nand" 12
NAND device
.IP "pos" 12
position of the block to mark bad
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Mark a block bad. This function is updating the BBT if available and
calls the low-level markbad hook (nand->ops->\fBmarkbad\fP).
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success, a negative error code otherwise.
